30/05/2007
BUDVA, Montenegro -- At an international conference that opened on Tuesday (May 29th), every country in Southeast Europe (SEE) acknowledged that EU integration is in their strategic interest and said they will co-operate to achieve it. 
European Parliament delegation head Doris Pack said the EU and Southeast Europe cannot exist without one another. 
She called on SEE leaders to find ways to accelerate the accession process. 
The presidents of Montenegro, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Macedonia, Albania, Bulgaria and Croatia attended the conference. 
(Vijesti - 30/05/07; Mina, Fena, RTRS, Makfax, HINA - 29/05/07)
